    {
        "desc": "Four earthen walls surround a sienna dirt courtyard large enough to accommodate\ndozens of horses and as many men. At the intersections of the walls, sturdy\nwooden ladders lead to and from a small ledge that runs the entire length of the\ndirt battlements, some fifteen feet above the ground. Deep ruts in the ground\nlead from the north gate to a large stable in the east, the result of numerous\nhorses passing into and out of this fort. Directly opposite of the north gate, a\nramshackle barracks has been constructed from wood, leather, straw and earth.\nScattered around the entrances to the barracks and the stables are various\nweapons and shields, all in desperate need of repair.\n",
