    {
        "desc": "A rectangular structure, constructed from a variety of building materials serves\nas barracks for the Rohir soldiers manning this fort. Overhead, thin wooden\nplanks are covered by hay, bound and braided together with leather straps, to\ncreate an effective roof. Old and worn cots line the southern and northern\nwalls. A large fireplace, no more than mud bricks stacked up at a hole in the\nwestern wall, warms and illuminates the long room. Armour, weapons and other\nsmall items are scattered about the room.\n",
